pesticide.PPE: long-sleeved shirt and long pants; waterproof gloves; shoes plus socks; protective eyewear; minimum NIOSH-approved particulate filtering facepiece respirator with any N, R or P filter, or NIOSH-approved elastomeric particulate respirator with any N, R, or P filter, or NIOSH-approved powered air purifying respirator with an HE filter

Active_Ingredients.name: Chromobacterium subtsugae strain PRAA4-1T cells and spent fermentation media

Safety_Information.general_Info: Causes moderate eye irritation. Avoid contact with eyes or clothing. Wash thoroughly with soap and water after handling and before eating, drinking, chewing gum, using tobacco or using the toilet.
Safety_Information.if_In_Eyes: Hold eye open and rinse slowly and gently with water for 15–20 minutes. Remove contact lenses, if present, after the first 5 minutes, then continue rinsing eye. Call a poison control center or doctor for treatment advice.
Safety_Information.physician_Note: Have the product container or label with you when calling a poison control center or doctor, or when going for treatment. You may also contact 1-800-222-1222 for emergency medical treatment information. For chemical spill, leak, fire, or exposure, call Chemtrec 1-800-424-9300.
